comments.text:
As an American with 47% of my DNA coming from the British Isles, I'm pleased to see that my cousins in the U.K. have discovered this delicious Mexican dish. I love chili and I make it often. It's so good, so cheap and so easy to make. 

F1nn, now that you're learning how to cook, you should tackle a dish known as Pate Chinois or French-Canadian cottage pie. It's like English cottage pie with fewer spices and fewer vegetables. The only vegetables are a 15-oz can of drained whole kernel corn, a 15-oz can of cream-style corn and a medium yellow onion that's been diced and fried until it's translucent. And the only spices are salt and pepper. The spices are minimal, but the dish is SO good.
